               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; first words (headings or parts of headings) of constituent texts; directives for the ministers; names of the ruling King, Patriarch and Metropolitan; abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
The text on pages 3r and 66r is written alternately in red and black lines.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The Ms. is composite, consisting of two production units: 1) fols. 1r-66v (texts I-II), 2) fols. 67r-76v (text III).</note>
                     <note>- Text I starts with the priest’s admonition Mi mäṭän... “How awesome...”. The excerpt from the "Book of the Testament" (30va-31rb) follows Text I without any separation, by rubrication or special heading.</note>
                     <note>- Anaphora of the Apostles (Text II-2) is present in a significantly abridged version.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
